            From voff
            v [km/s]  = voff × c
            Δλ [Å]    = voff × λ_center 

            From v [km/s]
            voff      = v / c
            Δλ [Å]    = (v / c) × λ_center


            From Δλ [A]
            voff      = Δλ / λ_center
            v [km/s]  = (Δλ / λ_center) × c

6/15 Pyqso example file experiments
Until stated otherwise assume source is spec-0332-52367-0639.fits
Note: After downloading and running files with no changes, the initial fits were worse than the ones documented in the 
github example, (ex: not mapping OIII for Hb). This was true for Noah and ID

decompose_host = False
- Added NL comp for Hb
- Altered BL comp for Ha, improved chi2
- Originally continuum (gold line) very poorly modeled data, now is a better fit
- When True
    - Host + qso temp is the total? Potentially affected by the PCA model
    - data - host is just the qso: theoretically what we want
        - If this interpretation is corrent then contiinuum is still poor but not as severe as orignally thought
            - Still a constant
            - FeII is better starting ~4000A
    - data is original observed
- When False
    - Only data, no data - host, no host, no host + qso line
    - Gold line continuum is no longer constant, could be better fit especially from 4500-5000A
    - NL and BL appear to follow FeII line very closely

decompose_host = False and poly = True to poly = False
    - Gold continuum is now a linear function
    - Broad line component is now veeeryy broad
    - NL now have smaller peak
    - Hb no narrow line component
    - BL now 2 unaligned components
    - Caused FeII "wiggle" to be more dramatic
    - Residuals appear to be based on FeII, NOT gold continuum

poly = True to poly = False
    - Ha fit worsened, NL no longer centered with data, closer to line_prior wavelength (6564.61)
    - Golden continuum not affected? Still appears to be a constant
    - Did not appear to affect the "model for the whole spectrum"

Fe_uv_op = False
    - Gold continuum no longer constant
    - Hb worse, OIII small completely skipped
    - Hb still no NL comp
    - BL split to 2 distinct components
    - Ha BL components adjusted, not as severe as decompose_host = False

Fe_uv_op = False, decompose_host = False
    - NL is again shifted towards given rest wavelength (6564.61)
    - Generally Ha NL very messed up
    - Lost 1 Ha BL componenet

Fe_uv_op = True to Fe_uv_op = False, decompose_host = False, poly = False
    - Golden continuum not linear?????
    - Residuals fairly poor (also poor for fe_uv_op_False_decompose_host_False)
    - Still missing Hb na and now missed OIII large
    - Hb BL got much smaller
    - Ha NL are back, bit too large

Fe_uv_op = False and poly = False
    - Hb Br too broad
    - Hb NL greatly improved
    - Residuals on top of qso data
    - Ha missing a NL component 
    - Ha NA reset to rest wavelength (6564.61)
    - Golden continuum not linear but worse than fe_uv_op_False

host_line_mask = False
    - Absorbtion lines/noise appeared in Ha and Hb
    - Hb potentially noisier but could also be change in scale
    - Worse fits for both
    - Appears to only have affected line fits and not host/qso/continuum lines
    
decomp_na_mask = False
    - Missing Hb OII large
    - OII appears to have been partally absorbed into main Hb and overinflated the broad line component

linefit = False
    - Continuum fitting with decompose_host == True did not appear to change from graphic, scale altered

BC = True and linefit = False
- decompose_host True vs False
    - QSO data is larger for False - bc the QSO data is no longer being subtracted from the host? yes that is exactly what is happening
    - Emission lines flux being overinflated in False bc of combination with host light
    - Error relatively the same for both
    - Continuum fits are okay for both


Conclusions:
- host_line_mask, decomp_na_mask, and BC affect the decomposition process and are therefore only relavent when decompose_host == True
- Fe_uv_op == False degraded the fit in all cases
- Fe_uv_op does not start until OII emission line at 3728.48 - maybe reduce wavelength range?
- decompose_host appears to better estimate the QSO light in the overall continuum
- BC == True doesn't appear to have a signficant affect on the blue end of the spectrum

Need to verify conclustions
- The gold continuum is power-law + polynomial continuum
- PCA models do improve continuum fit but idk how to add one/find/create one yet


